ZH: 我的开支超出了预算。
EN: My expenses exceeded my budget.

ZH: 他每月要为家庭开支付出大部分收入。
EN: He spends most of his income on family expenses every month.

ZH: 我们需要控制开支，以便节省更多钱。
EN: We need to control our expenses in order to save more money.

ZH: 她总是很谨慎地计划开支。
EN: She always plans her expenses very carefully.

ZH: 这笔额外的开支让我的银行账户陷入了困境。
EN: This extra expense has put my bank account in a tight spot.

ZH: 我们必须做出艰难决定来削减开支。
EN: We must make tough decisions to cut expenses.

ZH: 我的家庭开支相当庞大。
EN: My family expenses are quite substantial.

ZH: 需要控制公司的运营开支，以确保盈利。
EN: Controlling the operation expenses of the company is needed to ensure profitability.

ZH: 如果我们不加以节制，开支就会超出预算。
EN: If we don't restrain ourselves, expenses will exceed the budget.

ZH: 政府正计划削减一些开支来减轻财政压力。
EN: The government is planning to cut some expenses to ease financial pressure.

ZH: 这笔额外的开支让我感到很苦恼。
EN: This extra expense is causing me a lot of distress.

ZH: 在购物前，请务必慎重考虑你的开支。
EN: Before shopping, please carefully consider your expenses.

ZH: 我们必须制定一个详细的开支计划。
EN: We must develop a detailed expense plan.

ZH: 管理好开支对于财务健康至关重要。
EN: Managing expenses well is crucial for financial health.

ZH: 他们不得不减少一些不必要的开支。
EN: They had to cut down on some unnecessary expenses.

ZH: 我们需要节制一下，因为开支已经超预算了。
EN: We need to cut back because expenses have exceeded the budget.

ZH: 我们需要降低一些生活开支以节省更多钱。
EN: We need to reduce some living expenses to save more money.

ZH: 他们决定裁员以控制公司的开支。
EN: They decided to lay off employees to control the company's expenses.

ZH: 购买房屋将是我们未来最大的开支。
EN: Buying a house will be our biggest expense in the future.

ZH: 如果能控制住每天的开支，就能更好地管理财务。
EN: Managing finances better can be achieved by controlling daily expenses.
